A) if this is a brand new phone, get a root terminal and remove the disclaimer
  Settings -> Security {???} -> Dev Mode
  phone will restart after it is done installing
  you can just wait {about 2 minutes} once it prompts for:
    ~2.6MB additional installation required

  open a terminal
  devel-su #password is rootme
  disclaimer-cal remove View-openmode

B) reflash-phone {flashing/instructions}

C) run:

n9 -t
set-passwd
set-host
keygen.pl
sync-wifi
respawn-limit
packages
packages #to fix any debs that install in the wrong order
config-files
secret-keys
launcher-buttons
status-menu
packages.pl --reinstall extra #to fix mt-toggles
ext4-mydocs
gconf-settings
setup-cities
config-files again...
profile.pl
install-klomp
#reboot, to ensure timezone for messages
restore-contacts
restore-comm call #check times for timezone error
restore-comm sms
sync-mydocs
sync-home
sync-pidgin
sync-fbreader restore
fetch-klomp-lists restore
sync-swype restore
setup-vkb-toolbar
klomp-sync user@`n9`
#remove-aegis #reboots!
#reset-accounts
sync-mms
